# Day 4: Node.js Intro 🚀

## 📖 Introduction
This is my **Day 4 task** where I learned about Node.js basics and created my first simple API that returns "Hello, World!".

---

## 📝 Steps I Followed

### 1️⃣ What is Node.js?
Normally, JavaScript runs only inside the browser.  
With Node.js, JavaScript can also run on the computer directly.  
This makes it possible to build **servers, APIs, and backend applications** using JavaScript.

---

### 2️⃣ Install Node.js
- I downloaded the **LTS version** from [nodejs.org](https://nodejs.org).
- Checked versions:
 
  node -v
  npm -v


###File: index.js
  
const http = require('http');

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  if (req.url === "/api/hello") {
    res.writeHead(200, { "Content-Type": "text/plain" });
    res.end("Hello, World!");
  } else {
    res.writeHead(404, { "Content-Type": "text/plain" });
    res.end("Page Not Found");
  }
});

server.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log("Server is running at http://localhost:3000");
});

###Run Terminal:

  node index.js


###Output:
  Hello, World!



